notes: Bait|Atta, black phediole, Crematogaster. Video of Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis @ 200x|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33||http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-RLJZr1XR2I|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: ActiveSearch|11-12:30. Crematogaster, Pseudomyrmex (video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zvoU-BZ66gM), |5mEPE|Waypoint 194||Arrived and registered. Walked Sendero del Caro until first small peak after the trail splits (I`d gone to the right). Wet at the start, but VERY dry where I sampled. Windy, sunny and the temperature rose from 24 - 27C while I was sampling. All traps down at 8:22am. 41 km from here to Rincon, 25 to Cacao, and 21 to Orosi. 360 Gigapan taken between 2 & 3. Videos taken of the dominant Pheidoles (black and yellow). Crematogaster, Pseudomyrmex and the Labidus|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66906/|http://bit.ly/fFqImT |http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|

notes: Bait|Atta, black phediole, Crematogaster. Video of Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis @ 200x|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33||http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-RLJZr1XR2I|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Bait|Atta, black phediole, Crematogaster. Video of Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis @ 200x|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33||http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-RLJZr1XR2I|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Bait|Atta, black phediole, Crematogaster. Video of Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis @ 200x|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33||http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-RLJZr1XR2I|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Bait|Atta, black phediole, Crematogaster. Video of Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis @ 200x|Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33||http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-RLJZr1XR2I|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: ActiveSearch|8:30 - 12:30. P. apicalis, Eciton (video taken: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EMlNXAeeLOM)|20mEPE|Waypoint 191||1.25 hrs walk up to 970m (6:40 - 8:10). Traps out and bait down at 8:30 necessary to be back at 3:30 to leav safely and get gas in La Cruz. Rained all night and all morning on walk up - stopped at 9:00am though cloudy for the day (with wind). Large Eciton swarm came through at 10:20 and were on site until I departed. Filled and took over bait and traps at 2 and 3. Traps up and at 1:30. Malaise trap taken down.
